x4freetext: H+ ions from 0.4 to 1.6 MeV; H2+ and H3+ ions from
with 15N was bombarded with mono-energetic protons
and the yield of alpha-particles and quanta was
measured as a function of proton energy. Magnetic
spectrometer was used to separate the long-range
alpha particles from elastically scattered protons.
The quanta were detected using a Geiger-Muller
energy-equivalent target thickness in keV was
always measured at the 0.898 MeV resonance, either by
width at half maximum or by the area under the curve.
